# Protos Web — Design Language

Protos Web is **cosmic / neon / glassmorphism** on a dark space background. When
building or restyling UI, match this language and reuse patterns from the element
library (`design/references/README.md`).

## Palette (CSS vars, defined in globals)

- `--dark #0a0a1a` (bg) · `--dark-card #0f0f2a` (panels)
- `--primary #ff6600` (sunset orange brand accent) · `--secondary #8b5cf6` (purple) · `--accent #06b6d4` (cyan)
- `--light #e8e8f0` (text) · `--light-muted #8888aa`
- Neon effect palette: cyan `#22d3ee`, blue `#3b82f6`, purple `#a855f7`, magenta `#ec4899`, neon green `#39ff9e`

## Rules of thumb

- Dark space bg + glassmorphism panels: subtle blur, thin light border `rgba(255,255,255,0.06–0.08)`, rounded (`rounded-2xl`).
- Prefer glow / neon borders + soft shadows over hard lines.
- Animate only `opacity` + `transform` (see `dom-canvas-layers.mdc`). No animating width/height/top/left/heavy filters on large fixed layers.
- 3D/spatial → R3F in `src/components/three/**`. UI chrome/content → DOM.
- Framer Motion for DOM motion; respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Element library (always available)

Catalog of reusable element concepts lives in **`design/references/README.md`** and
in Supabase (`public.design_elements` table + `design-assets` storage bucket).

Categories: `text-animations`, `scroll-animations`, `page-transitions`, `card-layouts`,
`card-hover`, `card-hover-themes`, `card-bg-textures`, `hero-backgrounds`,
`animated-bg-patterns`, `lighting-backgrounds`, `parallax-layers`, `buttons`,
`navigation`, `modals`, `logo-treatments`, `icon-badges`, `dividers`, `service-icons`,
`blog-ui`, `about-assets`, `process-assets`, `loaders`.

When asked for a new UI element, first check the catalog for a matching pattern and
implement it in this visual language before inventing something new.
